subSubSection.paragraph:
HABITUS. Specimens usually bright green (
Fig. 2A
), often with finger-like projections (
Fig. 2B
). Surface hispid due to protruding spicules.

SPICULAE. Skeleton with two classes of oxeas: smooth megascleres (
Fig. 2C
) and spined microscleres (
Fig. 2D
). Megascleres fusiform, microscleres acerate (
Boury-Esnault & Rützler 1997
). Gemmuloscleres were not observed. Megasclere length 265 μm (190–375 μm), width 11 μm (2.5–20 μm) (
Fig. 2E
). Microsclere length 76 μm (50–117.5 μm), width 4.8 μm (2.5–7.5 μm) (
Fig. 2F
).
